    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And the fact that he-- that he weathered the-- the threatened ban by the [NON-ENGLISH], and that he actually, you know, had the guts to say, this is a situation where we have to cooperate with the godless Zionists, in my mind makes him a-- well, somewhat of a historic figure.",
      "word_count": 55
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] I-- I guess I didn't talk much about him during the-- during the interview.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And I-- I somehow feel I should have done more justice to him.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I guess there is one thing that-- which is a very personal thing to me.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The Jewish people today is somewhat divided about issues of peace and not peace.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But I've mentioned a few times to my friends that when in Bergen-Belsen I was unable to sleep at night--",
      "word_count": 20
    }
